You are giving it a rule that all anchor links inside of `.header-navigation ` need to be styled. Yet the child anchors are also part of `.header-navigation `. Therefore they will have that style unless you specify the style of anchors inside of `.nav-bar-item`

If you also add this:
```
.nav-bar-item a {
color: red;
}
```
Then the styles will only apply to the child anchors.

You should use the selector &quot;parent&gt;child&quot; (greater-than sign):

    .header-navigation {
        padding-top: 30px;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;

        &gt; a {
            font-family: &quot;Playfair Display&quot;, serif;
        }

        ...

You currently using the &quot;parent child&quot;-selector (space sign), that applies style to all following child- and child-child-elements of the parent.
See [`element&gt;element`][1] and [`element element`][2]


  [1]: https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/sel_element_gt.asp
  [2]: https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/sel_element_element.asp

