The format string needs a pair of braces for *each* literal brace.

    &gt;&gt;&gt; &#39;{foo}&#39;.format(foo=3)
    &#39;3&#39;
    &gt;&gt;&gt; &#39;{{{foo}}}&#39;.format(foo=3)
    &#39;{3}&#39;
    &gt;&gt;&gt; &#39;{{{{{foo}}}}}&#39;.format(foo=3)
    &#39;{{3}}&#39;

If you *only* want braces around something, then it has to be an even number of braces:

    &gt;&gt;&gt; &#39;{hi} {{foo.bar}}&#39;.format(hi=3)
    &#39;3 {foo.bar}&#39;

